{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = Jennifer Des | nationality = Belgian | occupation = photographer, | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1975|03|11}} | birth_place = [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]] }}
'''Jennifer Des''' (born 1975) is a Belgian photographer.
==Style== She is inspired by [[Francis Bacon (artist)]] in the treatment of the human corpse by manipulating images of [[plastic surgery]].<ref>[http://www.younggalleryphoto.com/photography/des/des.html The mutilated corpses]</ref>
==Biography== Born in [[Brussels]], she studied at the '''École de recherche graphique''' in her hometown. She put into practice her studies in [[Kinshasa]] where she worked for six months for the [[French Community of Belgium]]. She had her first individual exhibition in 2003 at the ''galerie Pascal Polar'' in Brussels. She was selected for the collective exhibition ''175 years of Belgium'' by the Belgian Photography Museum and at the ''Espace Blanche'' <ref>[http://www.espaceblanche.be/crbst_84.html Espace Blanche]</ref> with [[Frédéric Beigbeder]] as her mentor. She exposed with [[Wim Delvoye]] and [[Delphine Boël]] at the Salle des Beaux Arts du [[Sablon (Brussels)|Sablon]] for the ''[[Pierre Bergé]] – [[Yves Saint Laurent (designer)|Yves Saint Laurent]] Foundation'' in 2007.<ref>[http://be.linkedin.com/pub/philippe-lichtfus/20/980/254 Concept Interview with Philippe Lichtfus]</ref> She made in 2009 an exhibition ''Les Sangtiments'' at the ''Young Gallery'' with her human body work from pictures made (with special admission) from parts of the human body found in the clinic rooms of hospitals.<ref>[http://www.lesphotographes.com/interviews/jennifer-des-expose-ses-sangtiments Young Galery ]</ref> In 2012 she had her exposition in the SohoPhoto Gallery in [[New York City]].<ref>[http://www.sohophoto.com/exhibitions/archive/december-2012-exhibitions SohoPhoto Gallery]</ref> Now Jennifer Des is working on the high-definition photography of the personalized [[iris (anatomy)|iris]] on a [[cosmos|cosmic]] background for the EYE-D project exhibited at the ''Mercedes House'' <ref>[http://www.mercedeshouse.be/fr/event/mercedes-house-concerts Mercedes House concerts p.6]</ref> in 2011, at the ''Top Marques'' in [[Monaco]] in 2014 and at the ''Café de Paris'' in [[Monte Carlo]] March 2015.<ref>Monaco Hebdo, 5 March Number 915, p. 43</ref> In May 2015 at the Park Lenôtre [[Mougins]] with [[Robert Hossein]] and [[Jean-Paul Belmondo]]<ref>[http://comtesse-tatiana.com/mecenat-prix/#asso Comtesse Tatiana]</ref> Invités d'Honneurs. She had an exposition in March 2016 in the Dark Room Galerie <ref>[http://www.darkroomgalerie.fr Dark Room Galerie]</ref> with [[Irina Brook]] and [[Soulwax]].<ref>[https://online.tribuca.legal/online/2016/10/834/#/30 Tribune Bulletin côte d'azur]</ref> <ref>[http://www.channelriviera.com/cr2/ Channel Riviera]</ref> <ref>[http://www.channelriviera.com/cr2/Article/5291/Darkroom_Galerie_un_regard_sur_la_Vie_un_clin_d_%c5%93il_a_l_Eternite Channel Riviera Web TV]</ref> <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=7&v=wwskb3W7Ah8 Galerie Dark Room Vernissage]</ref> <ref>[http://www.radiochalomnitsan.com/upload/podcasts/audios/570505fac7d183.64622224.mp3 Radio explication du concept EYE-D]</ref>
